  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\nWhen replying to a long message, user can't send more than ~8 lines because the send button is hidden behind the keyboard. I could only replicate it on Android. The amount of lines that can be send is probably related to the device screen size.  \r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/47293696-22b3e780-d60b-11e8-8f67-121f05ff2b14.png\" width=\"200\">\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nThe send button is always visible and the message just is scrolled when new lines are added. \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nThe send button becomes invisible at some point of a long message when replying to a long message. \r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\nTry to reply with a long message (more than 8 lines) to a long message (more than 8 lines) in 1-1 or public chat.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: Oct 22, nightly\r\n* Operating System: Android\r\n* Tested on Android, Galaxy S8.\r\n",
